**Library Version:**

com.afollestad.material-dialogs:core:3.3.0
 
**Affected Device(s):**
 
Only tested on Moto G5s+ & Nexus 5X
 
**Describe the Bug:**

Calling uncheckAllItems followed immediately by checkItem(items) leaves the dialog with all items unchecked. 

**To Reproduce:**
```
private fun MaterialDialog.setChecked(checked: IntArray) {
    uncheckAllItems()
    checkItems(checked)
}
```

**Expected Behavior:**

The dialog should have checked items as specified by the `checked` IntArray

---

It'd be nicer if there was a build it adapter method to set checked items. Something like the below (untested)
```
  override fun setCheckedItems(indices: IntArray) {
    val indicesToAdd = indices.filter {
      check(it >= 0 && it < items.size) {
        "Index $it is out of range for this adapter of ${items.size} items."
      }
    }
    this.currentSelection = indicesToAdd
    if (existingSelection.isEmpty()) {
      dialog.setActionButtonEnabled(POSITIVE, true)
    }
  }
```

