```java
new FolderChooserDialog.Builder(MainActivity.this)
                .chooseButton(R.string.md_choose_label)  // changes label of the choose button
                .initialPath("/")  // changes initial path, defaults to external storage directory
                .tag("path-tag")
                .show();
```
 
### Reproduction Steps

1. Create a new FolderChooserDialog and set it's initialPath in the root directory ("/")
2. Build and open the application
3. You can now see, in the folder list, a "...", also if you are in the device root

### Expected Result
We shouldn't see these dots, infact normally you cannot go up if you are in the root folder


### Actual Result
The app crashes due to a NullPointerException because the canGoUp boolean is true at the first dialog start. if you try to enter in a random directory and to go up, you cannot see the "..." because canGoUp = false

